*30th Anniversary of Jong Holland 1949
Competition: Friendly
Season: 1949

BlockSource: http://www.rsssf.com/tablesn/nedamahist.html

* On the occasion of the 30th anniversary of Jong Holland, founded 15 July 1919 in Willemstad.
* The two clubs entering were both runners-up in the last domestic championship (BVV Den Bosch in the Netherlands 1948/49 and Atlético Junior in Colombia 1948). All matches played in Willemstad.


7/30/1949; Curacao; 3-0; Aruba; Willemstad, Curacao

7/31/1949; Guatemala; 2-4; Atletico Junior de Barranquilla; Willemstad, Curacao
Notes: Date Uncertain

8/2/1949; Aruba; 1-3; BVV Den Bosch; Willemstad, Curacao

8/5/1949; Curacao; 1-1; Guatemala; Willemstad, Curacao

8/6/1949; BVV Den Bosch; 0-0; Atletico Junior de Barranquilla; Willemstad, Curacao
Notes: Atlético Junior walked off at 0-0 in 83' when BVV Den Bosch was awarded a penalty; the referee awarded the match to BVV Den Bosch but as a sporting gesture BVV Den Bosch agreed to count the match as a 0-0 draw

8/7/1949; Aruba; 0-2; Guatemala; Willemstad, Curacao

8/9/1949; Curacao; 2-0; Atletico Junior de Barranquilla; Willemstad, Curacao

8/11/1949; Guatemala; 3-1; BVV Den Bosch; Willemstad, Curacao
Notes: Date Uncertain

8/13/1949; Aruba; 2-3; Atletico Junior; Willemstad, Curacao
Notes: Date Uncertain

8/14/1949; Curacao; 1-1; BVV Den Bosch; Willemstad, Curacao

* Final Table:
*  1.Curaçao           4  2  2  0  7- 2  6
*  2.Guatemala         4  2  1  1  9- 7  5            
*  3.Atlético Junior   4  2  1  1  7- 6  5
*  4.BVV Den Bosch            4  1  2  1  5- 5  4           
*  5.Aruba             4  0  0  4  3-11  0      

* NB: in 1952, BVV Den Bosch again played the Dutch Antilles, during their tour of the Netherlands in preparation for the Helsinki Olympics.


